						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Nioreh wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">...and NES_CHR_BANKS to 4 (or as many as you have)</div><br />Try to use powers of 2 though, since emulators have a hard time dealing with weird ROM sizes (understandably so, since real chips always come in powers of 2). In the case of CNROM you can safely have 1 (pointless, because that'd be the same as NROM), 2 or 4 CHR-ROM banks.</div>

